##Leukemia patients in Wuhan City

Micro signal

Function description, we are with you in this battle

No platelets, and the mother's blood is failing. Always shy of begging, devoted to her mother, Wen began to rescue, "in the face of such natural and man-made disasters, my mother, such a patient, may become the 'cost' of whatever the cost. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Wei Chao Tsui

At the request of the party concerned, the voice has been handled

It was the night of January 30th.

Her mother, a patient at acute leukemia, has been attending the hospital for the past two years. On the 28th, her mother's platelet count was only 15, compared to 150-300 in the normal population.

Platelet count is the life line of Leukemia patients. Below 20, the patient needs an external platelet transfusion. Otherwise, the body is at risk of bleeding. And once the internal bleeding occurs, life is difficult to salvage.

Because of the changes in Wuhan Epidemic Situation, the Department of Hematology of Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University has been suspended, and the inpatient department no longer treats patients with hematological diseases. Xiaowen and her father asked the major blood department hospitals in Wuhan, but no one can admit her mother, for the mother transfusion life-saving blood.

The only solution, says the doctor, is for Wen's mother to go to the emergency room with a fever to check for the new pneumonia virus, and if not, arrange a blood transfusion in the emergency room.

People with leukemia have a weakened immune system. Even a small cold can be life-threatening. South Central Hospital of the fever emergency, do is the new pneumonia virus fixed-point test kit. With Small Wen mother's immunity, see a doctor here, extremely easy occurrence cross-infection, consequence is unimaginable.

The only solution was a dead end for her mother.

"If my mom doesn't make it, this story doesn't have to go out, " she told me on the evening of January 31, just after our interview.

The following is based on Xiaowen's statement:

Bad feeling

On January 23rd, at 9:30 in the morning, I received a message on my cell phone from the Wuhan Government.

30 minutes to lockdown. I immediately told my parents, "Mom, Dad, Wuhan is closing down, we need to stock up on some grain. " At the same time, I had a hunch, "if this epidemic can not be controlled, it is likely that the blood will be strained. "

I thought mother's blood transfusion during the Spring Festival would be a problem, and there would be a long line. But what she didn't realize was that she was now facing a situation where there were no platelets to lose.

On January 26, my mother's platelet count was 35. Doctors at the Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University said that if my mother's blood condition worsened, she would need to be hospitalized for blood transfusion. By January 28, I again took my mother to south-central hospital for blood tests, the mother's platelet count has been as low as 15.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Inspection report

My mother is a hematologic department of old patients, but because of the epidemic, central South Hospital in-patient department no longer receive blood patients. The doctor on duty advised me to find another hospital for blood transfusions.

Then I immediately sent wechat to the former tube bed doctor, he said the hospital flat all stopped, the emergency is now receiving and sending fever patients. If my mother does not have other circumstances, the suggestion is at home, avoids because of the immunity low and infects the virus.

I said to him, "you know my mother's blood condition, her platelets have been on the infusion, do not lose or keep falling, it is likely to fall to zero, then what? "

The doctor still said that there is no way, "can only be now this way, you either go to other hospitals, or first observation. "

He also said that they had been treating patients with blood diseases for so long that they knew my fear that if they bled, it would be too late.

Looking for life-saving blood

When I got home, I kept contacting other hospitals in Wuhan to find platelets for my mother.

The provincial cancer hospital, they didn't have a designated hospital, they didn't have a suspected case, but the doctors just refused. "We don't take blood diseases, " he said.

Doctors in Tongji said that the resources for this epidemic are very limited, and there is very little blood. In principle, they do not accept patients from outside, "I can't even get blood for my own patients, there's a long waiting list for appointments, and we don't have the energy or resources to take care of patients from other hospitals. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Notice of delay in opening a clinic in Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University

I contacted the Provincial People's Hospital, the Central War Zone Hospital, Tongji, concord, and their other branches, as well as the provincial cancer hospital, the Ninth Hospital, Puaipuren Hospital.

The response from the doctors at these hospitals was pretty much the same: All the staff were there to support the outbreak, and we didn't have the staff to take in any more patients in the wards. We don't have anyone.

I understand, my mother is seriously ill, the hospital will suspect my mother is not latent period patients, there must be such a possibility. These two days called asked a lot of hospitals, hospitals have the mentality of self-preservation.

Faced with this situation, my mom didn't say anything, or maybe she didn't want to show it to me. Sometimes we fight because the pressure is too much.

My mom always felt that if she left, it would be a relief for me and my dad. She thinks she's been holding me back too long.

I'm a very strong person, so I don't like to ask for too much help from others. It's a negative emotion to vent to your friends and talk about your home situation. Render too much, others will think you like Xianglin sister-in-law in the same non-stop nagging. I don't like this.

But I'm not ready to give up. Now although the blood pressure, but as long as the hospital can put my mother in, my mother can not be in the hospital, transfusion platelet away.

In the current weather in Wuhan, I can push my mother to the open air to lose. Half an hour with a bag of platelets, and now we don't have a chance.

It's hard to give up

Two years ago, my mother was diagnosed with MDS EB2. At that time, the doctors even judged that, with my mother's blood and the level of chemotherapy, it might not last three months. But my mom kept going.

From the onset of my mother, my father and I know we must do a good job of infection prevention, so our home early with ultraviolet light disinfection. My mother wore a protective mask 24 hours a day and slept in it as long as her Oxygenation lasted. My father and I are the same, the last two years in the outside never took off the mask.

That's only part of it. My mother gargles with salt water every hour of the day, especially after three meals. Regardless of defecation and urine, all must use saline to wash Gargle, is to prevent oral and perianal infection.

These were all the precautions I could see, and we did everything we could to pay attention.

Mother in south-central Hospital attending physician, we have been particularly good, with all our efforts to cure. He often praised me and my father for looking after my mother. In the attending physician and our joint efforts, my mother two years through many times the door have survived, the spirit is also good.

For two years, Little Wen's Mother's bill

But then something like this happened, and I couldn't believe it.

You know what? It's like something you've been trying so hard to protect, and then all of a sudden, it breaks. And it was broken by accident, not because I didn't do it right. It's not even mom's progression.

Last night I had no choice but to call the doctor at central South Hospital again. The doctor knows that my mother is an old patient. He said he would like to keep an extra bag of type O platelets for my mother every day in the way of emergency treatment. Once my mother dies, as long as she can be sent to the hospital, as long as the hospital can receive it, he can be in the emergency treatment, to transfuse platelets into my mom.

I've come this far.

In the old days, my mother could survive on a cycle of medical care. But in the face of such natural and man-made disasters, patients like my mother, may become at all costs in the middle of the "cost. ".

In the last two days, this feeling has been getting stronger.

("Wen" is a pseudonym)

During the day, February 1st, when the script was being typeset, Mandy contacted me again.

The information she posted online was seen by a doctor in charge of the hospital. He told her to delete the post as soon as possible because it would have a "negative impact" on the hospital.

The latent rule of leukaemia treatment circle is the first medical responsibility system, other hospitals do not admit treatment, go to the South Hospital fever emergency treatment for the mother is also a dead end, small Wen feel that they are close to the limit.

She said to me: "My mother and I have nowhere else to go, this article must be published. Since determined to die, can not be unclear. "
